     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is your basic twilight denial deck. It uses Moria Swarm to get cards out quickly.<br>
<br>
Free Peoples<br>
   Basically, I bid 2. If i go first or if my opponent starts prancing pony I start boromir and pippin and pull Aragorn. If its not prancing then i start aragorn.I try to get the stuff out early and cut down on twilight.If i need to double move i can get rid of lingering baddies with Gondor&#39;s Vengeance or if i have aragorn&#39;s bow I kill em off with RV. Try to double move.When u have the no stranger to shadows and bill and talent out and i double move and an able guide and deft in the regroup they usually have little twilight to use.I usually try to move 1-3;4;5-6;6-8;9.<br>
<br>
Shadow<br>
   Basic Moria swarm.Play schimitars and runners to add more twilight to get a cave troll out and some beats. <br>
<br>
This deck cycles very well and is fun to play.I hope u enjoy it too. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
